                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'd love to be able to solo Servitor of Luclin.  It seems like all the ingredients are there to make it feasible:
<br />

<br />
It's easy enough to run around the zone invisible... Servitor himself seems to be the only thing that sees invisible.  There are several named in the zone that drop the key to Servitor's door easy enough, but you can just stand outside the door and '/target servitor' to target him if you want to.  Khemot Agarthizar (or his PH) spawns right outside Servitor's door (not close enough to aggro Servitor).  Khemot is rootable but not mezzable.  Khemot is charmable but only with CoD, and his MR is merely normal.
<br />

<br />
There are two (occasionally three) mobs in the room with Khemot, easily disposed of.  The room next to that has no spawns, a perfect place for buffing and preparing.  There are several long hallways nearby too for getting distance, but those might not be quite as safe.
<br />

<br />
But... Servitor has 100k HP.  Even with him slowed and Khemot hasted I can't imagine he'd die before my pet.  Trying to grab another pet with Servitor chain summoning me doesn't sound like much fun.  Gating out and coming back in time to grab another pet before he heals doesn't seem very likely either (but I'm no expert).  So... I'm doubting I could do it.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
