                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I soloed the FG shard at the platform with 2 Warriors. Started by cramming myself into the SW corner there and Tashing the closest Warrior, and mezzing it, then mezzing the other one, and also tashing it. When mez was about to break I charmed the first one, and then waited to sic it on the second.
<br />

<br />
The fight took about 5 minutes, keeping the opponent rooted in the corner, with one charm break. First round went perfectly, opponent died with pet at 7% health. I broke charm and nuked/rooted twice to kill it. No shards.
<br />

<br />
Waited for the respawn (30 minutes?) and tried again with the same tactic. Unfortunately, my pet started winning by a large margin, and had nearly 25% health left when the other was dead. I knew I'd never be able to nuke it dead before it managed to crawl into the middle of the room, so I checked the body - and it had a shard. Gated out in triumph. I don't think I took a single point of damage the whole time.
<br />

<br />
For the ME shard, I ran my little Ranger over and checked track. I saw that the Savant was up and attempted to pull it somewhere safe with my Enchanter, but could never get an opening. Eventually I tried and got about 4 adds and the Savant, who DoTted me good and I had to zone. When DoTs wore off, I had less then 20 HP remaining. Close call!
<br />

<br />
A few hours later I checked again, and the Savant was still up, so I enlisted a Monk to assist me. After a killing some of the trash he got the Savant and one add to a safe spot and I helped kill it with a charmed bat. Looted the shard and gave the Savant's staff to my Ranger.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
