                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yay me, I'm done <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> I had help on Acrylia Caverns and Sshraza Temple (Ranger and Cleric).
<br />

<br />
So here's some thoughts.  Listed from easiest to hardest
<br />

<br />
Dawn Shroud Peaks - Charming one of the green NPC's is the way to go on this one. 
<br />

<br />
Scarlet Desert - The Trojegs outside of the Reavers make great pets. Look for Tro Jeg Fireservants. Good level, proc, and either doesn't cast or doesn't cast often.
<br />

<br />
Fungus Grove - I had the worst trouble with this until I saw Morpheus's post on Guard Jontroy. He doesn't summon and hits for about 420, significantly more than anything else in the Shiknar caves. I just had him mow through everything. I did have a little trouble on my first pull because I didn't break charm and he insisted on fighting every grove of mushrooms i passed, but with some good navigation that can be avoided too.
<br />

<br />
The Grey - As long as you've invested time in an EB item, this should be cake. Lot's of DC or regular charm mobs to choose from. I'd go for a shisshar revenant.
<br />

<br />
Seru - This one took me a while, but not as long as a lot of other people. I think the biggest tip here is that higher level does not necessarily make a better pet. I noticed that when I charmed a dark blue summoning mob up top (55ish?) he didn't seem to have anymore HP or do more damage than the DC bait I found up there. Pick someone that's all ready dual wielding like suggested and you should do fine. 
<br />

<br />
The Deep - So far I haven't reached any that I thought was difficult yet, the only challenge in this one was getting up to the bridge as there are large pockets of mobs with random see through invis ones on the way to it. Once your at the bridge, I'd reommend pulling to the right. There is one static spawn shroom and no wanderers so he makes a good pet. I can't remember what I got my shard off of, but I don't think it was either mob Cennyan mentioned. It was a thought horror model and it was 1 of the 4 static mobs right next to the bridge though. 
<br />

<br />
Maidens Eye - Add's are the only real problem here. I camped next to AR and while fighting a battlemaster my pet got feared and ran across the zone (think it was a xi xaui add). I was afraid someone else might get to it before I did so I ended up trying to pull it from the middle of the zone where it stopped several times and zoning each time before it wandered back to it's spawn point by iself. From there it was an easy pull. Watch out for adds and if it's cloaked you might want to consider having your pet rooted as much as possible. 
<br />

<br />
Acrylia Caverns - I used some friends to help with this one. I managed to make it into the inner caves using pacify and invis, but I'm not used to fighting solo in closed in spaces. I killed about 4 or 5 before i was running low on mana from charm breaks and reruning my self and decided to just bail. Came back later with a Ranger and Cleric that also needed shard and did really well. I just used my animation and pulled. The ranger had no problem tanking. 
<br />

<br />
Akheva Ruins - I solo'd my shard here, but I stayed away from the traps as best I could. Pick a corner and pull the shade reavers from the west room.  I had a little more trouble getting my container but also manged it solo. Setting off traps is the big problem here but you do need some new tactics based on the pacification changes. Instead of pacifying the mob of the ledge, I mezzed it. I then proceeded to pacify the 2 nearest chanters in the room and remezzed the mob I was standing next to. After BCBing the remains, I looked for the invis guy. If he wasn't there, I remezzed the guy next to me one last time, walked back to the west wall, and camped. I strongly recommend camping out each time. It's easier on mana since you can't just pacify the mob for 7 minutes, and you don't have to worry about traps because you aren't actually running across the zone. You could probably just as easily keep remezzing but I felt safer just camping out. When my guy finally did appear, I pacified the 3 nearet guys on the ground and the closest one up top. FYI, the top row does need to get pacified. Getting close enough to the invis mob will agro those that aren't pacified. In my case I had 2 on me instantly (1 pacified). I handed in my wisp stone and immediatly handed in my emerald and just trained out to zone. You do not need to do the text. 
<br />

<br />
Sshraza Temple - This was was rather frustrating, the twists and turns in the hall with mobs behind corners made single pulling difficult. Even when I swung my camera out and pacified everything I regularly pulled 2 or 3 mobs every time. On top of that, most mobs are hasted and Sowed (or Shrewed) so they move fast and hit reasonably hard. We cleared the caves twice (Ranger, Cleric, Rogue, and myself) before we got 4 shards.
<br />

<br />
Edit - I mislabled Acrylia caverns and Akheva Ruins. Corrected it now.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Maelific on Thu Apr 01, 2004 9:26 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
